      <div class="SOTTO_PARA"><a name="DUC50ffbdf02b7610058c4387d9909970d2"></a>Removing the swinging arm
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8065"> </a>Before removing the concerned parts, you must first carry out the following operations:
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8068"> </a>Remove the silencers. <a href="79882.html#DUC408fed082b2310058d65a5fdf30dcfc4">Removing the silencer</a>.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8073"> </a>Remove the rear wheel (<a href="78610.html#DUC64d8fb602aeb100584ccb8bb6ec21ad2">Removing the rear wheel</a>).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8078"> </a>Remove rear sprocket (<a href="80840.html#DUC35a1fd282b87100583a689ec0e3196d2">Replacing the rear sprocket</a>).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8083"> </a>Remove the rear brake calliper (<a href="78655.html#DUC6ea2fad82aff1005805fa1973a55c3d2">Removing the rear brake calliper</a>).
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8088"> </a>Remove the shock absorber (<a href="80788.html#DUCa4657f682b7410058c2887d9909970d2">Removing the rear shock absorber</a>) for the base version.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8093"> </a>Remove the shock absorber (<a href="80790.html#DUCd04ac1b02b7410058c2a87d9909970d2">Removing the rear shock absorber</a>) for Pikes Peak, Granturismo or Touring versions. 
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8098"> </a>Refit the rear mudguard (<a href="78010.html#DUC24c226b82aab10058bbef20939ae18d2">Removing the rear mudguard</a>).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8104"> </a>Remove the rear eccentric hub as described in â€œ<a href="80802.html#DUCc1bbd2c82b7510058c3087d9909970d2">Removing the rear wheel eccentric hub and the rear wheel shaft</a>".
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8109"> </a> Loosen screw (A) and remove the top grommet (B); release rear brake hose and rear speed sensor cable from swinging arm by
            loosening screws (1) and collecting cable clips (2).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_026903411.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8114"> </a>On Pikes Peak, Granturismo and Touring versions, grommet (B) houses rear brake hose, rear speed sensor cable and rear accelerometer.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_038303421.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8119"> </a>It is possible to check the supporting bearing play while the swinging arm (3) is still fitted on the motorcycle frame.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8121"> </a>Grasp the rear of the swinging arm (3) and try to move it in the four directions shown by the arrows.
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_027003412.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8126"> </a>Any abnormal movement is a sign of worn bearings that could cause bike instability.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8128"> </a>Once the play in the support bearings has been checked, the rear swinging arm&nbsp;(3) may be removed from the motorcycle.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8130"> </a>Hold the swingarm shaft (4) with the screws (5) on the bike LH side, and loosen at the same time the screw (5) on the opposite
            side: recover the washer (6).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_027103413.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_027203414.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_027403415.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8140"> </a>Using the drift no. <span class="bold">88713.1074</span>, fully extract the swingarm shaft.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8145"> </a>Remove the swinging arm (3) assembly from the frame.
         </div>
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8147"> </a>Undo the screws (7) to remove the lower chain sliding shoe (8) from the swingarm (3).
         </div>
      </div>
      <div class="AggancioFigure">
         <center><img class="Default" src="img/DUC_MO_MTS1200_7_027503416.jpg"></center>
      </div>
      <div class="SOTTO_PARA">
         <div class="Testo"><a name="d3e8152"> </a>Undo the screws (9) to remove the chain guard (10) from the swingarm (3).
         </div>
      </div>
